{"word":"ἀποκλαίω","slug":"ἀποκλαίω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀποκλαίω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to weep aloud</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>ἀπ. στόνον</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><el>ἀπ. τινα</el> or <el>τι</el> <i>to bewail much, mourn deeply for</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>ἀποκλαίεσθαι κακά</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>τὴν πενίαν</el> <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, also, <i>to cease to wail</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}